-- Indian shares gain over 2 pct to record highs on exit polls
-- By Abhishek Vishnoi and Indulal PM
-- Tue May 13, 2014 02:33AM EDT
-- None



MUMBAI, May 13 (Reuters) - Indian shares rose as much as 2.2 percent on Tuesday, a third consecutive record high, as stocks of companies focussed on the domestic sector surged after exit polls showed the Bharatiya Janata Party and its allies winning a majority in the elections.

The NSE index <.NSEI> rose as much as 2.25 percent to hit a record high of 7,172.35. The BSE index <.BSESN> rose as much as 2.2 percent to hit a record high of 24,068.94, surpassing the psychologically important 24,000 mark for the first time. [ID:nL3N0NY0XT]